        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-04-19 23:51:46.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2\n> \n> We should not be adding a second version of toJsonString().  If there is a defect in SvcLogicContext.toJsonString, it should be corrected there instead.\n\nGood point, totally agreed, we have submitted the revision accordingly.\n\nBy the way, I wouldn't describe this as a defect, SvcLogicContext.toJsonString is merely not robust enough. because when multiple DGs are reading/writing the same context memory, it is easy to introduce corrupted context memory record that toJsonString's JsonParser has difficulty with. What we do in this patch is basically filter the context memory first and then only restore the records to JsonObject, for those keys with the provided prefix\n\nAgain, thanks for the review. any comments are welcome.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
