        "timestamp": "2021-04-22 23:58:46.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nGood point, totally agreed, we have submitted the revision accordingly.\n\nBy the way, I wouldn't describe this as a defect, SvcLogicContext.toJsonString is merely not robust enough. When multiple DGs are reading/writing the same context memory, it is easy to introduce corrupted context memory record that toJsonString's JsonParser has difficulty with. What we do in this patch is basically filter the context memory first and then only restore the filtered records to JsonObject.\n\nThanks again for the review. any comments are welcome.",
